-- Mellanox Surges Most in Two Weeks, Closes Gap With U.S. Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-01T10:10:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-01/mellanox-surges-most-in-two-weeks-closes-gap-with-u-s-shares.html
  Mellanox Technologies Ltd. (MLNX) , an
Israeli developer of technology used to transfer and store data,
rose the most in almost two weeks, closing the gap with the
U.S.-traded shares.  The  shares  gained 3.8 percent, the biggest intraday advance
since June 19, to 279.20 shekels, or the equivalent of $71.40,
at 12:44 p.m. in  Tel Aviv . The New York-traded stock advanced
6.2 percent to $70.821 on June 29.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  